Upgrading Eggdrop
=================

Back up your config, userfile, and chanfile before upgrading. They
should not be overwritten, but it never hurts.


Standard upgrade
----------------

1. Read NEWS for new/changed settings.
2. Build the new version (see INSTALL).
3. Update your config file with any new settings.
4. Restart the bot.


Migrating from .conf to .toml
------------------------------

Your existing .conf files continue to work unchanged. Migration is
entirely optional.

Why migrate:
  - No Tcl knowledge needed to configure the bot
  - Clean key = "value" syntax
  - Organised sections: [bot], [servers], [channels], ...
  - No chmod u+x or shebang needed
  - Interactive wizard for new installs

Method 1 — automated:

    python3 scripts/conf2toml.py mybot.conf mybot.toml

Method 2 — start fresh:

    eggdrop --setup mybot.toml

Method 3 — manual reference:

    .conf (Tcl)                      .toml (TOML)
    ────────────────────────         ────────────────────────
    set nick "MyBot"                 [bot]
    set owner "MyNick"               nick  = "MyBot"
                                     owner = "MyNick"

    server add irc.net +6697         [servers]
                                     list = ["irc.net:+6697"]

    channel add #mychan              [channels]
                                     list = ["#mychan"]

    loadmodule server                [modules]
    loadmodule irc                   load = ["server", "irc"]

    source scripts/foo.tcl           [scripts]
                                     load = ["scripts/foo.tcl"]

    unbind dcc n simul *dcc:simul    [tcl]
                                     commands = ["unbind ..."]

Underscores in TOML map to dashes in eggdrop variables:
  botnet_nick → botnet-nick, help_path → help-path

After migration:

    eggdrop -m mybot.toml    # first run
    eggdrop mybot.toml       # subsequent runs


Breaking changes (devinkbrown fork)
------------------------------------

Build system:

  Meson + Ninja replaces autoconf/make. The old ./configure && make
  workflow does not exist. See INSTALL for the new process.

Config format:

  The default config file is eggdrop.toml (was eggdrop.conf). Legacy
  .conf files are still loaded when passed explicitly on the command
  line. The bot auto-detects format by file extension.

  eggdrop --setup generates a ready-to-use TOML config interactively.
  No chmod or shebang needed.

Random number generation:

  random()/srandom() has been replaced with getrandom(2) (Linux) or
  arc4random_buf (BSD/macOS). The randint() macro is now a static
  inline function producing cryptographically secure output.
  Third-party modules using random() should switch to randint(n).

Safe integer parsing:

  All raw atoi() calls are replaced with egg_atoi(), a safe strtol
  wrapper defined in eggdrop.h. Third-party modules should use
  egg_atoi() instead of atoi() — it handles non-numeric input without
  undefined behaviour.

Password hashing:

  Eggdrop has deprecated the blowfish module for password hashing in
  favour of PBKDF2. See doc/PBKDF2 for migration instructions.

Server syntax (upstream v1.10):

  The old "set servers {}" syntax was replaced with "server add" in
  v1.9. In TOML, use [servers] list = ["host:port"].

Botnet TLS:

  Since v1.9, SSL botnet links require an explicit '+' port prefix.
  Use .chaddr to update your ports if you want encrypted links.


Breaking changes (upstream v1.10)
----------------------------------

  - The -n flag for terminal mode was removed (use -t instead).
  - copy-to-tmp and quick-logs config options were removed.
  - The old DNS module config section was removed.


